main event: A single unidentified object was observed hovering and then departing in a southerly direction over Deer Park, Maryland on March 28, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 10 minutes.
The object was described as a small, round white light about 1/8 inch in diameter at the distance it was seen, moving smoothly and steadily across the sky before disappearing over trees.
The witness was unable to estimate the speed of the object, but estimated it was approximately 500 yards away.
The witness did not have any photographs or physical evidence of the sighting.
The report was filed as a 'FAIL CR' conclusion, indicating the sighting could not be conclusively explained.
